Preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.Rub the asparagus with olive oil and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Heat a griddle pan until hot, then griddle the asparagus with the garlic and herbs until chargrilled all over. Remove from the pan, discard the rosemary and thyme sprigs and set aside.Score a border 1cm/Â½in around the edge of the pastry and prick inside the border with a fork.Place the pastry onto a baking sheet and bake in the oven for five minutes, or until the pastry is beginning to turn golden-brown and is slightly risen.Place the goats' cheese onto the middle of the pastry and top with the griddled asparagus.Transfer to the oven and bake for 12-15 minutes.To serve, place onto a serving plate.